              "items": [
                {
                  "id": "https://colenda.library.upenn.edu/items/ark:/81431/p3zp3wm11/manifest/annotation/p5",
                  "type": "Annotation",
                  "motivation": "commenting",
                  "body": {
                    "type": "TextualBody",
                    "value": "<p>1</p>\n            <p>Brethren! Were it my province to address an audience of non-Israelites,<lb/> I would,\n                on the present occasion, select as my text a weighty sentence<lb/> which occurs in\n                the 14<hi rend=\"sup\">th</hi> chapter of Exodus. It is the following <add>דבר אל זני\n                    וכ\"ו</add><lb/>\n                <add>מים על ים</add> “The Eternal said to <persName>Moses</persName>, wherefore\n                criest<lb/> thou unto me,? Bid the children of <placeName>Israel</placeName> go\n                forward” When dearly bought<lb/> freedom is in jeopardy; when the angry billows of a\n                political sea im=<lb/>=pede the march of civilization, and the adversaries of human\n                brotherhood<lb/> are skillfully <sic>marshalled</sic> for the onslaught, deeds of\n                self-denial more<lb/> than psalmody<add>?</add> will sanctify the life of man. The\n                Lord of hosts will<lb/> be extolled by the efforts which tried to uphold truth, more\n                than by<lb/> the fervent utterance of the lips. Let him therefore who values\n                his<lb/> country's honor speed on, let him trustingly follow the path which<lb/>\n                leads to national deliverance, and when the happy goal shall have<lb/> been\n                attained, raise the anthem which will be reverberated <add>ה' הושיעה המלך יעננו ביום\n                    וגו'</add><lb/> from sea to sea, even from the <placeName>Atlantic</placeName>\n                to the <placeName>Pacific Ocean</placeName>.<lb/> Thus would I briefly speak this\n                day, and dismiss <del>a</del> the <hi rend=\"underline\">greater</hi> assemblage.<lb/>\n                But as my lot was cast among those who are singled out in their<lb/> belief and\n                their worship, I deemed it expedient to adopt a different<lb/> course. A\n                non-compliance of the Hebrew Community with the<lb/> counsel of the\n                    <persName>President</persName> of the <placeName>United States</placeName>,\n                might at this jun=<lb/>=cture, have been open to animadversion. It therefore\n                became</p>"
                  },
                  "target": "https://colenda.library.upenn.edu/items/ark:/81431/p3zp3wm11/canvas/p5"
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
