              "items": [
                {
                  "id": "https://colenda.library.upenn.edu/items/ark:/81431/p3zp3wm11/manifest/annotation/p6",
                  "type": "Annotation",
                  "motivation": "commenting",
                  "body": {
                    "type": "TextualBody",
                    "value": "<p>2</p>\n            <p>fit that we, who in our devotional outpourings at this solemn<lb/> season,\n                    <del>ever</del> tearfully remembered the sorrows of\n                    <placeName>America</placeName>, that we, who ceaselessly<lb/> pray for the\n                welfare of the land of our adoption, and testified the love<lb/> we bear it, when at\n                the first summons of the Executive we swelled the<lb/> ranks of her defenders, it\n                became imperative, I say, that we should<lb/> nevertheless your own voices, this day\n                also, to that of our fellow-citizens who<lb/> implore God for the restoration of\n                peace. And verily, my friends!<lb/> Whatever opinion we may entertain touching the\n                appositeness of the<lb/> request, our acquiescence therein <del>will</del> can be\n                but the prompting of our<lb/> responsive <del>sentiments</del> feelings. This\n                country, which many of you<lb/> claim at that of their birth, and some as that of\n                them choice, has<lb/> not, like others that vaunt liberality, doled out her benefits\n                to<lb/> you, O descendants of <persName>Jacob</persName>! but she has generously\n                invited you<lb/> to participate in all the exuberance of her goods; hence, you as\n                you did glory<lb/> in her happiness, <del>and</del> grieve over her distress. And\n                when the custodian<lb/> of her liberties, descrying imminent danger, exhorts to\n                prayer that it may be<lb/> averted, you who taught the world how to pray, will even\n                at this hour<lb/> exclaim as you are wont <add>אולי</add>. “Save us O Lord,\n                answer<lb/> us O King on this day that we call upon thy name”. But in<lb/> attuning\n                our hearts to the national supplications, we receive an addition<lb/>=al incentive,\n                in the present instance, by the remembrance that the<lb/> Chief Magistrate of our\n                beloved Union, did not transcend the proper <del>his</del> limits, to</p>"
                  },
                  "target": "https://colenda.library.upenn.edu/items/ark:/81431/p3zp3wm11/canvas/p6"
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
