                  "type": "Annotation",
                  "motivation": "commenting",
                  "body": {
                    "type": "TextualBody",
                    "value": "<p>5</p>\n            <p>the tocsin resounds which tells the world that the pioneer of civil<lb/> and\n                religious liberty is verging on a precipice, men—<del>shall I call them<lb/>\n                    men</del>, no, heartless and soulless beings—are found, who will turn<lb/> to\n                profit the mighty struggles of the brave to escape the yawning gulf?\n                No<del>y</del>,<lb/> let others enumerate the sins which have exposed the country of<lb/>\n                <placeName>Washington</placeName> to the contumely of the stranger and the horrors\n                of war.<lb/> I will rather deplore them and acknowledge the justice of the Divine<lb/>\n                <del>?</del> verdict <add>דרכיו ראיתי וארפאהו ואנחהו ואשלם נחמים לו\n                ולאבליו</add><lb/> “For the inequity of his covetousness was I wrath, and smote him,\n                I hid<lb/> myself and was indignant, for he went on forwardly in the way of<lb/> his\n                heart”. This sentence of <persName>Isaiah</persName> so applicable to your\n                unhappy<lb/> condition, O my hearers, reveals the plague which has putrified\n                the<lb/> channels whence have sprung these waters of <placeName>Meribah</placeName>\n                (contention). Yet, it lies<lb/> in your power to convert them again into refreshing\n                streams of <add>Hebrew</add><lb/> brotherhood. God showed you the tree that will\n                sweeten those<lb/> bitter waters, in the example of your immortal predecessors.<lb/>\n                Let the memory of their sterling virtues cluster around your minds, and<lb/> awaken\n                them to deeds of magnanimous valour, let them counsel<lb/> the renunciation of all\n                preconceived <del>thoughts</del> notions for the preservation of<lb/> this palladium\n                of human rights, the total subjugation of selfishness<lb/> for the\n                    <del>benefit</del> prosperity of the common country, the repudiation of all</p>"
                  },
                  "target": "https://colenda.library.upenn.edu/items/ark:/81431/p3zp3wm11/canvas/p9"
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
