                  "motivation": "commenting",
                  "body": {
                    "type": "TextualBody",
                    "value": "<p>6</p>\n            <p>doctrines subversive of the principles which they who framed the<lb/> Declaration of\n                your independence unequivocally for the spread of civilization enunciated; then\n                will<lb/> you regain the attitude from whence you were ruthlessly &amp; unnaturally\n                    <del>cast</del> forced down,<lb/> or, to continue in the language of the prophet\n                “God will see your ways and<lb/> heal you, He will guide you securely, and restore\n                comforts to you and those<lb/> who mourn for your sorrows <add>Hebrew</add><lb/> And\n                this day which a spirit of meekness has devoted to sacred communion,<lb/> will be\n                the opening of a new era, glorious to <placeName>America</placeName>, and\n                fruitful<lb/> of joy to the whole <hi rend=\"underline\">human race</hi>.</p>\n            <p>Lord God! who didst bless this land with Thy favour, restore her, we<lb/> beseech\n                Thee, to Unity. Cancel her inequities, and let her be distinguished<lb/> anew for\n                the virginal purity of her pristine years. Grant that<lb/> charity and truth may\n                weave the garland that shall adorn her children,<lb/> for then will righteousness\n                and peace be met in her midst clasped in each<lb/>\n                <del>mutual, others</del> others' embrace. Guide Thou the steps which are now\n                wending toward<lb/> the conquest of national supremacy over faction, that they may\n                not<lb/> overreach the bounds justly prefixed. Oh! Eternal Being who didst<lb/>\n                rekindle <del>the long suppressed</del> feelings of love in the bosom of the\n                fierce<lb/> son of <persName>Isaac</persName>, breathe into us words of brotherly\n                reconciliation, and let the hand<lb/> that wields the sword be <del>mutually,\n                    grasped</del> fraternally seized with a mutual grasp <del>fraternal\n                    pressure</del>. At this<lb/> hour, when the heart of a whole nation is upheaved\n                to Thee, calm<lb/> O Omnipotent! its inward perturbation. Regard the prayer\n                which</p>"
                  },
                  "target": "https://colenda.library.upenn.edu/items/ark:/81431/p3zp3wm11/canvas/p10"
                }
              ]
            }
